sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant FE as Web Frontend
    participant API as MfaController
    participant M as MfaApplicationService
    participant R as Redis
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant E as Email Service
    participant A as Audit Platform

    Note over U,R: User has a restricted session that only permits MFA enrollment endpoints.

    U->>FE: choose TOTP or secondary email
    FE->>API: POST /mfa/enrollments
    API->>R: validate restricted session and endpoint scope
    R-->>API: valid
    API->>M: beginEnrollment(type)
    alt TOTP
        M->>M: generate secret
        M->>R: store encrypted pending secret + enrollment TTL
        M-->>API: QR/otpauth URI shown once
    else Email MFA
        M->>M: generate OTP and hash
        M->>R: store hashed OTP + pending email
        M->>E: send verification OTP
        M-->>API: masked destination
    end
    API-->>FE: enrollment challenge

    U->>FE: submit verification code
    FE->>API: POST /mfa/enrollments/{id}/verify
    API->>M: verifyEnrollment(code)
    M->>R: load pending enrollment atomically
    alt invalid or expired
        M-->>API: AUTH_MFA_INVALID_CODE / expired
    else valid
        M->>DB: BEGIN
        M->>DB: create/activate MfaMethod
        M->>DB: clear enrollment and reenrollment flags
        M->>DB: COMMIT
        M->>R: consume enrollment challenge
        M->>A: mfa.enrollment.completed
        M-->>API: completed, require continuation/fresh login
    end
